# waypoint supports two map-data providers, chosen with MAPS_PROVIDER.
# A .env file is OPTIONAL — the default provider is free and keyless.

# Which backend to use: "osm" (default, free, no key) or "google" (paid).
# MAPS_PROVIDER=osm

# --- osm provider (default) ---
# Free, keyless OpenStreetMap services. Override only to point at your own
# (e.g. self-hosted) instances:
# NOMINATIM_URL=https://nominatim.openstreetmap.org
# OSRM_URL=https://router.project-osrm.org
# OVERPASS_URL=https://overpass-api.de/api/interpreter

# --- google provider ---
# Required when MAPS_PROVIDER=google. Create a key in Google Cloud Console with
# the Directions API and Places API enabled, and billing turned on.
# GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your-api-key-here

# Optional: a separate key for the frontend map (Maps JavaScript API), since
# this one is visible in the browser and should be restricted by HTTP referrer
# rather than the server-side key's IP restriction. Falls back to
# GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY above if unset.
# GOOGLE_MAPS_BROWSER_KEY=your-browser-restricted-key-here

# --- sign-in + pro tier ---
# waypoint supports "Sign in with Google" (no client secret needed — the
# frontend gets a signed ID token straight from Google via Identity Services,
# and the server verifies it itself). All of this is OPTIONAL: with none of it
# set, the app runs exactly as above, free tier only, no sign-in UI shown.

# OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Web application) from Google Cloud Console > APIs &
# Services > Credentials. Add your app's origin(s) to "Authorized JavaScript
# origins" (e.g. http://localhost:5173 for local dev). This ID is public and
# gets sent to the browser via /api/config.
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# Secret used to sign the app's session cookie (any long random string).
# Without this, a random secret is generated per process start, which means
# everyone is signed out on every restart/deploy — fine for local dev, set a
# real value in production.
# SESSION_SECRET=change-me-to-a-long-random-string

# Signed-in users can flip a "Pro" toggle in the UI to use Google Directions +
# Places (via GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY above) and a richer weather forecast
# (OpenWeatherMap One Call 4.0, humidity/UV/visibility) instead of the free
# OSM + Open-Meteo stack. There's no real subscription/billing check behind
# this — any signed-in user can enable it — it's a demo of what a paid tier
# would look like. The pro tier only appears once BOTH keys below (and
# GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY above) are set; either one missing keeps the app
# free-tier only.
#
# OpenWeatherMap requires a separate opt-in subscription ("One Call by Call")
# for One Call 4.0, even on its free tier (1,000 calls/day):
# https://openweathermap.org/api/one-call-4
# OPENWEATHERMAP_API_KEY=your-openweathermap-key-here
